    "type": "message",
    "text": "This is interesting because it is a written language that is a mix of pictograph and spatial relationships to tell a story.\n\nOne common argument against visual programming languages is that popular writing systems are the most efficient way to communicate, therefore programming should be text, but this is a good example of a writing system that is \"visual\" in the way we think of visual programming languages",
